{
    "content": "Thirty-ninth: Quoting the book of Jam’ al-Shatat, al-Kaf’ami has reported Imam al-Sadiq (‘a) as saying: If you had intended to report one of our sayings but Satan made you forget it, you may put your hand on your forehead and say this supplication prayer:\r\n\r\n--صَلَّى اللهُ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَ اٰلِهِ، اَللّٰهُمَّ اِنِّىْۤ اَسْاَلُكَ يَا مُذَكِّرَ الْخَيْرِ وَ فَاعِلَهُ،وَ الْاٰمِرَ بِهِ،ذَكِّرْنِىْ مَاۤ اَنْسَانِيْهِ الشَّيْطَانُ‏--In the book of man-la-yahzuruhul-faqih, Imam al-Sadiq (‘a) is reported to have said that whoever is frequently unmindful in his prayers, may say these words when he enters the toilet:\r\n\r\n--بِسْمِ اللهِ،اَعُوْذُ بِاللهِ مِنَ الرِّجْسِ النَّجِسِ الْخَبِيْثِ الْمُخْبِثِ‏ الشَّيْطَانِ الرَّجِيْمِ۔", 
